<dl id="s12004af"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="us12" href="#s12004af">Cyclops: </a><a href="../../FF/unbs/s12all.htm#s12004af">sector 4(af)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> joy of grief</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">But, Carril, raise the voice on high; tell the deeds of other times. Send thou the night away in song; and give the <mark>joy of grief</mark>. <small> James MacPherson, <a name="JMPOU" href="/udra/udex.htm#JMPOU"><cite title="source">The Poems of Ossian</cite></a> (1806), Lz17, Ln254</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: To give &ldquo;the joy of grief&rdquo; generally signifies to raise the strain and soft and grave music; and finely characterizes the taste of Ossian&apos;s age and country. </mm> </dd></dl>
